/-
KERNEL-PURE SAT DEMONSTRATION (ROUND-2026-07-14, Task A / WS2).

This standalone file (NOT part of the `Lean617` library â€” `lake build` does not
touch it) demonstrates that the SAT primitive M9's unsatisfiability has a genuinely
KERNEL-CHECKED, axiom-pure proof via Mathlib's `lrat_proof` (`Mathlib.Tactic.Sat.FromLRAT`).
`lrat_proof` replays the LRAT certificate by BUILDING A PROOF TERM that the Lean
kernel typechecks â€” no `native_decide`, no `ofReduceBool`.

Run:  cd lean617 && lake env lean KernelPureDemo/Demo.lean

Expected `#print axioms m9_kernel_pure`:
    'm9_kernel_pure' depends on axioms: [propext, Classical.choice, Quot.sound]
i.e. ZERO reflection axioms â€” the certificate is checked by the kernel alone.

PROVENANCE of the two assets (both regenerable, exact commands):
  * M9.cnf       â€” the canonical DIMACS emitted from the Lean definition `MCNF 9 18`
                   (sha256 596ffcfbfcb709d691a6d97fed415ce7d015f64f95c48cf963cbeb9be9d618cb,
                   matches tools/certgen/checksums.txt). Regenerate:
                     lake env lean --run ../tools/certgen/emit_cnf.lean M 9 18 M9.cnf
  * M9.core.lrat â€” a fresh CaDiCaL 3.0.0 re-solve, backward-trimmed to the UNSAT
                   core by our ext/drat-trim (17010 core lemmas, gapped ids â€” fine
                   for `lrat_proof`, which keys clauses by stated id):
                     cadical M9.cnf M9.drat --binary=false --quiet --unsat --inprocessing=false
                     ext/drat-trim/drat-trim M9.cnf M9.drat -L M9.core.lrat   # "s VERIFIED"

MEASURED COST (this machine, 64GB): 495s wall, 14.0GB peak, for M9's 17010-lemma core.

WHY THIS IS NOT (YET) WIRED INTO `primFacts`. `primFacts` consumes `(MCNF 9 18).Unsat`
