the kernel: `example : (MCNF 9 18).clauses.size = 39743 := by rfl` TIMES OUT at >400s even
with `maxRecDepth 1000000` â€” the identical obstruction that made `native_decide` necessary
for the primitives in the first place. And even setting the bridge aside, the two large
primitives are out of reach on memory: nonex11/nonex12 have 325MB/455MB raw certificates
(hundreds of thousands of lemmas) while M9's mere 17010 lemmas already cost 14GB here.
So the four SAT primitives retain `native_decide` (see FORMAL.md "KERNEL-PURE MIGRATION"
and tools/axiom_allowlist.txt for the exact accounting). This file is the end-to-end
validation that the kernel route itself is sound and axiom-clean at the scale it can reach.
